figgy.title: Generate a report of all Figgy resources which have MMS-IDs that no longer resolve in the catalog

comments.body: Reminder to recepient of the report: Opening the .csv directly in Excel risks corrupting the MMSID, which may be converted to scientific notations. [Import it](https://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/msoffice/forum/all/data-corruption-issue-when-editing-csv-files-with/b2e8a31e-12fc-4d39-9fbd-435b9d832865) instead to avoid the corruption.

The last bit of housekeeping is the new webfile share needs to be writable by www-data. Right now on the staging site you get errors like: ![Screenshot 2023-07-12 at 8.47.57 AM.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5cba088397df763a9090ce23/d1be98ee-3972-44d6-9427-79515375ba6f)

comments.body: The issue comes from the import configuration we have for library databases from libguides. Descriptions should be imported as html rather than plain text. The linked PR updates the configuration for the importer. In this instance the "Best Bet" content type referenced the Worldcat Database content type which is where the description rendered is pulled from.
Deployed to staging.
